cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT. 

This paper deals with counting problems in combinatorics, which is a common theme in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of counting graph homomorphisms is also closely related to computational complexity (cs.CC), as the complexity of this problem and its variants have been extensively studied. The paper also involves graph theory (cs.CG) and algorithms/data structures (cs.DS) in its analysis of the complexity of the #_p GraphHom(H) problem. Finally, the paper touches on topics in graph theory and topology (cs.GT) by considering the properties of square-free graphs and trees.
